The whole is cased in a massive oak & leather trunk that I believe to be original to the gun. The trunk has a lift-out tray with a lot of accessories. There are 8 bores and then there are other 8 bores but one would have to go a fair distance to come up with a more solid gun than this Holland & Holland with barrels that are in superb condition inside and out.

title: For Sale/Trade:  H&K Mark 23 .45 Auto (less than 20 Rnds fired!)
postcontent:
My loss is your gain here. It's absolutely a fantastic firearm as well as an elusive piece to many collectors due to its price point and discontinued production.

The mark 23 is a civilian production of the infamous MK23 USSOCOM that serve as the primary offensive weapon for the navy seals and special ops. (Also known to many metal gear solid fans and movie buffs familiar with Tears of the sun)

Skipping the history lesson now, feel free to read up on Google if you'd like, let's get to the good stuff ;)

I'm looking more so to Trade this beast for something a little more carry friendly, and while this was a very fun and comfortable range toy, its just too D*** big to tote around on a daily basis. 
Bottom line, throw me some offers if you've got something in reliable condition, between calibers of 9mm and .45 and a holster to match you should be talking to me.

Also, if its cash you're looking to spend I'll negotiate with reasonable cash offers. I promise to still be the cheapest you'll find this particular firearm in the us. (But the better deal is just a flat trade) I'm not looking to capitalize on this, its just not practical for what I need.

Comes with one factory magazine with 12rd capacity
Operators manual and a locking sentry box
Level II safariland kydex holster converted for OWB use
Can even toss in the remaining Winchester jhp rounds if you wanna make a quick victory stop at the range on the way home.

Extreamly clean and in the few years I've owned this beauty, I've only put two mags through the handgun and the rest of the time its been sleeping in the nightstand or locked up in the hall closet. I want to start carrying and the two times I've took it on errands its just not felt right. I'm a lanky guy so it stands out like a colostomy bag on spring break, and prints like a horrible shoplifting attempt. CC is not happening with this gun to say the least.

Usual stuff here, no felons, must be 21+ and able to show an I'd with proof of Arizona residency. I'm not the federal govt and am happy to arm a legal us citizen but there's these little.things called rules and laws. 

Shoot me your trades or cash offers through text and let's both make a deal worth dancing about

(5.......2.....0....37.......1....6..8...6..1) 
                                                                
                                                                    

Will trade for:
                                                                            Show me what you've got that's suitable for.daily carry and preferably a .45 but I'll consider 9mms too. Needs to have a holster or I'll ask some cash to cover a decent one (I won't gouge for it) an extra Mag or two wouldint hurt but not.a deal breaker. Newer Gen Glocks are nice too. Just show me what you've got.
